<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The second paper is &#8220;<a href="https://astro.theoj.org/article/157501-rapid-cosmological-inference-with-the-two-loop-matter-power-spectrum">Rapid cosmological inference with the two-loop matter power spectrum</a>&#8221; by Thomas Bakx (Utrecht U., NL), Henrique Rubira (Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität, DE), Nora Elisa Chisari (Utrecht) and Zvonimir Vlah (Ruđer Bošković Institute, Croatia). This was also published on Tuesday February 10th in the folder <a href="https://astro.theoj.org/section/1188-cosmology-and-nongalactic-astrophysics">Cosmology and Nongalactic Astrophysics</a>. This paper uses the COBRA method to compute the two-loop effective field theory power spectrum of dark matter density fluctuations, providing more precise cosmological constraints than the one-loop EFT.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The overlay for this one is here:</p>


